The games industry is no stranger to overhyped disappointments and overpriced and unfinished releases. Despite this, The Lord of the Rings: Gollum managed to up the ante. Not just by releasing the worst game of the year so far by a mile (sorry Redfall) but by somehow managing to botch their apology. I'm so fascinated by this.
